title._content: Buenos Aires Statue of General San Martin

description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "General San Martin was one of the great patriots and liberators of South America from Spanish rule. After his death his body was brought to Buenos Aires and reverently placed in a tomb, one of the handsomest in the world, about which stand three marble figures representing Buenos Aires, Chile, and Peru."
